------------------------------

Description:
============

The "zslapack" collection of algorithms are 
adaptations from real(8) LAPACK algorithms for
complex symmetric matrices, 
i.e. complex matrices with A(i,j)=A(j,i)

The interfaces are analogous to the corresponding real symmetric interfaces

Without deeper analysis, we found that essentially mechanical 
carry over of the real symmetric algorithm works for
a limited class of tests. 

!!! DISCLAIMER !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
The algorithms have only been tested for limited uses 
for our purposes and come without any warrenty whatsoever.
!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!


Extension of the library
========================
The following strategy was found to be convenient:

(1) Collect in the directories dblas and dlapack all files 
    needed for the REAL version of a given algorithm to work; 
    test in a routine like the diagon.f90 supplied

(2) Copy the main new routine into zlapack, only rename the 
    ROUTINE from d**** to zs*****, WITHTOUT renaming the FILE
    Write a call to it into examples/diagon.f90 and compile.
    The compiler will complain, supply the missing routines by the same
    prodecure.

(3) Test the result versus the REAL version and versus more general 
    complex lapack routines

